All but one of the 21 specimens of this species included in the analysis were collected from the Azores;
the remaining specimen came from Scotland. Thus, our sample represents only some of the more northern elements of the distribution of this species, which occurs throughout the eastern Atlantic from Norway to Gabon . The analysis yielded essentially a single cluster. The range in pairwise differences among specimens in this cluster was 0–8, with an average of pairwise differences of 2.5
.
